It’s understood some infrastructure was damaged by the fire at the fabric filter plant. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom says its investigating the cause of the fire which broke out at its Kusile Power Station in Mpumalanga. It’s understood some infrastructure was damaged by the fire at the fabric filter plant.  The power utility says the extent of the damage will still be assessed. No injuries were reported. Eskom spokesperson Dikatso Mothae said, “There was a fire yesterday that was extinguished, and no incidents were reported. the matter is being investigated.”